import requests
import bs4
import json

# helper function to get the soup object from a url
def get_soup(url):
  response = requests.get(url)
  soup = bs4.BeautifulSoup(response.text, "html.parser")
  return soup

def scraper(url):
  # get soup object
  soup = get_soup(url)

  # create dictionary to store the data
  data = {}

  # get all the question summary items
  question_items = soup.find_all("div", class_="question-summary")

  # loop through the question items
  for item in question_items:
    # extract question title
    question_title = item.find("a", class_="question-hyperlink").text
    # extract tags
    tags = item.find("div", class_="tags").text.strip().split()
    # extract user name
    user_name = item.find("div", class_="user-details").find("a").text

    # add data to dictionary
    data[question_title] = {"tags": tags, "user_name": user_name}

  # print data as JSON
  print(json.dumps(data, indent=2))

if __name__ == "__main__":
  url = "https://math.stackexchange.com/questions"
  scraper(url)
